.SH "NAME"
Text::ProgressBar:::Timer \- displays elapsed time
.SH "VERSION"
.IX Header "VERSION"
version 0.2
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    use Text::ProgressBar::Timer;
\&
\&    my $bar = Text::ProgressBar\->new(widgets => [Text::ProgressBar::Timer\->new()]);
\&    $bar\->start();
\&    for my $i (1..150) {
\&        sleep 0.1;
\&        $bar\->update($i+1);
\&    }
\&    $bar\->finish;
.Ve
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Widget which displays the elapsed seconds. It is super class of '\s-1ETA\s0'
and 'FormatLabel'. An example of default settings:
.PP
.Vb 1
\&    Elapsed Time: 0:0:8
